description: Manage frontend IP addresses of an application gateway.

commands.name: az network application-gateway frontend-ip create
commands.syntax:
az network application-gateway frontend-ip create --gateway-name
                                                  --name
                                                  --resource-group
                                                  [--no-wait {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                                  [--private-ip-address]
                                                  [--public-ip-address]
                                                  [--subnet]
                                                  [--vnet-name]
examples: az network application-gateway frontend-ip create -g MyResourceGroup --gateway-name MyAppGateway -n MyFrontendIp --public-ip-address MyPublicIpAddress

az network application-gateway frontend-ip create --gateway-name MyAppGateway --name MyFrontendIp --private-ip-address 10.10.10.50 --resource-group MyResourceGroup --subnet MySubnet --vnet-name MyVnet

commands.name: az network application-gateway frontend-ip delete
commands.syntax:
az network application-gateway frontend-ip delete --gateway-name
                                                  --name
                                                  --resource-group
                                                  [--no-wait {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
examples: az network application-gateway frontend-ip delete -g MyResourceGroup --gateway-name MyAppGateway -n MyFrontendIp

commands.name: az network application-gateway frontend-ip list
examples: az network application-gateway frontend-ip list -g MyResourceGroup --gateway-name MyAppGateway

commands.name: az network application-gateway frontend-ip show
commands.summary: Get the details of a frontend IP address.
examples: az network application-gateway frontend-ip show -g MyResourceGroup --gateway-name MyAppGateway -n MyFrontendIp

commands.name: az network application-gateway frontend-ip update
commands.syntax:
az network application-gateway frontend-ip update --gateway-name
                                                  --name
                                                  --resource-group
                                                  [--add]
                                                  [--force-string {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                                  [--no-wait {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                                  [--private-ip-address]
                                                  [--remove]
                                                  [--set]
                                                  [--subnet]
                                                  [--vnet-name]
examples: az network application-gateway frontend-ip update --gateway-name MyAppGateway --name MyFrontendIp --private-ip-address 10.10.10.50 --resource-group MyResourceGroup

commands.name: az network application-gateway frontend-ip wait
commands.summary: Place the CLI in a waiting state until a condition is met.
